+     * visible tiling anywhere, so the whole model is treated as CLAMP in
+     * practice. This exact HSF asset (same bitmap names) is also
+     * bootDll/opening.c's OpeningMdlId[0]; both extrude the same way.
+     *
+     * That plain extrude still left a real, measured black notch near the
+     * top/bottom-center edge at wide aspect -- and the notch was seen to
+     * MOVE between the top-center and bottom-center edge across two
+     * captures of the same static screen taken ~20s apart, confirming this
+     * asset's own slow ambient motion shifts where the shortfall shows up
+     * over time, not a fixed static gap. A first attempted fix (more of
+     * the same isotropic growth via an extra multiplier) was confirmed
+     * WRONG by recapture -- it made the backdrop mostly vanish instead of
+     * closing the gap. Root cause: this backdrop is not a flat plane -- its
+     * 5 sub-objects span real local-Z depth, and isotropic scaling grows Z
+     * by the same factor as X/Y; the deepest sub-object's own farthest
+     * point already sits within roughly 100 units of this scene's far clip
+     * (15000) at the plain scale_factor() this project ships, so any extra
+     * Z multiplier pushes it past the clip and this engine's own per-object
+     * cull check drops the whole sub-object. This also plausibly explains
+     * the original notch itself: the backdrop's own ambient motion can walk
+     * a marginal sub-object across that same threshold as it plays, with no
+     * widescreen-side change at all. Real fix: grow only X and Y by
+     * scale_factor() and leave Z completely untouched
+     * (mp6_widescreen_extrude_model_xy()) -- identical contribution on the
+     * two axes that matter for screen-space coverage, with no depth-clip
+     * risk regardless of window width. Every other extruded scene (Party
+     * mode, title, mode-select, and opening's own identical-asset call)
+     * still goes through the plain, fully-isotropic
+     * mp6_widescreen_extrude_model(), byte-unchanged. */
+    mp6_widescreen_extrude_model_xy(lbl_1_bss_2D8[1]);
